==========================
CONTEXT API DATA FLOW
==========================

                    App.js
                       │
                       │
        Creates the user object
                       │
                       ▼
             UserContext.Provider
        value = { name, role }
                       │
                       │
         Shares data with all child components
                       │
                       ▼
                 Dashboard.js
                       │
                       │
      Does NOT receive or pass any props
                       │
                       ▼
                  Profile.js
                       │
                       │
      Does NOT receive or pass any props
                       │
                       ▼
                 UserInfo.js
                       │
                       │
       useContext(UserContext)
                       │
                       ▼
   React finds the nearest Provider
                       │
                       ▼
        Returns the user object
                       │
                       ▼
      Display name and role on the UI


==========================
STEP BY STEP FLOW
==========================

Step 1

UserContext.js

createContext()

↓

Creates an empty Context object

↓

Exports UserContext

Purpose

Creates a shared container that stores shared data.


--------------------------------------------------

Step 2

App.js

Creates User Object

↓

user

↓

<UserContext.Provider value={user}>

Purpose

Stores the data that should be shared with all child components.


--------------------------------------------------

Step 3

UserContext.Provider

Receives

value={user}

↓

Makes the user object available

↓

To every child component

Purpose

Acts as the data provider for the component tree.


--------------------------------------------------

Step 4

Dashboard.js

Receives Nothing

↓

Passes Nothing

↓

Simply renders Profile

Purpose

Acts as a normal component.

No prop drilling.


--------------------------------------------------

Step 5

Profile.js

Receives Nothing

↓

Passes Nothing

↓

Simply renders UserInfo

Purpose

Acts as a normal component.

No prop drilling.


--------------------------------------------------

Step 6

UserInfo.js

useContext(UserContext)

↓

React searches upward

↓

Finds UserContext.Provider

↓

Reads value={user}

↓

Returns user object

↓

Display

user.name

user.role

Purpose

Consumes the shared data directly.


==========================
COMPLETE INTERNAL FLOW
==========================

Application Starts

↓

UserContext Created

↓

App Executes

↓

Creates User Object

↓

Provider Receives User Object

↓

Provider Stores User Object

↓

Dashboard Renders

↓

Profile Renders

↓

UserInfo Renders

↓

useContext(UserContext)

↓

React Searches Upward

↓

Nearest Provider Found

↓

Reads value={user}

↓

Returns User Object

↓

UserInfo Receives Data

↓

Displays Data

↓

Browser Shows UI


==========================
HOW REACT FINDS THE CONTEXT
==========================

UserInfo

↓

Needs UserContext

↓

Looks at Parent

(Profile)

↓

Provider Not Found

↓

Looks at Parent

(Dashboard)

↓

Provider Not Found

↓

Looks at Parent

(App)

↓

UserContext.Provider Found

↓

Reads value={user}

↓

Returns User Object


==========================
BEFORE CONTEXT API
==========================

App

↓

Dashboard(user)

↓

Profile(user)

↓

UserInfo(user)

Every component receives and forwards the user prop.

This is called Prop Drilling.


==========================
AFTER CONTEXT API
==========================

                 UserContext
                      │
                      ▼
              Provider (App)
                      │
          ┌───────────┴───────────┐
          │                       │
     Dashboard               Other Components
          │
          ▼
       Profile
          │
          ▼
      UserInfo
          │
          ▼
 useContext(UserContext)
          │
          ▼
  Reads Shared Data Directly


==========================
MEMORY TRICK
==========================

createContext()

↓

Provider Shares Data

↓

Child Calls useContext()

↓

React Searches Upward

↓

Nearest Provider Found

↓

Reads value

↓

Returns Shared Data

↓

Component Displays the Data